t_condition.incomplete",{"lettering":57,"dimensions":58},"Described by Orsi as fine, small, regular characters of the fourth or third century BCE; Alpha has straight bar; Epsilon has shorter middle bar; omicron is smaller than other characters and mid-line; sigma is four-bar with top and bottom strokes angled moderately outwards, middle strokes extending almost full-width.",[59,64],{"type":60,"l":61,"from":62,"to":62,"unit":63},"letterHeight","Line 1","line1","mm",{"type":65,"l":66,"from":62,"to":67,"unit":63},"interlinear","Interlineation line 1 to 2","line2",{"_":69,"notBefore":70,"notAfter":71,"evidence":72},"Fourth or third century BCE on the basis of lettering.",-400,-201,"lettering",[74,79],{"_":75,"type":76,"ref":77,"region":78},"Syracusae","ancient","http://pleiades.stoa.org/places/462503","Sicilia",{"_":80,"type":81,"ref":82,"region":78},"Siracusa","modern","http://sws.geonames.org/2523083",[84],[85,86],37.08415,15.27628,{"_":88,"type":89,"subtype":90,"when":91,"geo":92},"Found in Orsi's excavations at the Temple of Olympian Zeus, Siracusa, between 6 April and 6 May 1893 (although the inventory states March 1893).","found","discovered","1893",[93,94],37.051605,15.257322,[93,94],{"_":97,"type":98,"subtype":99,"geo":17},"None","observed","autopsied",{"_":101,"type":102,"subtype":103,"geo":17},"Not located to date","not-observed","lost",[105],{"n":106,"url":107,"height":108,"width":109,"desc":110,"surfaceType":111},"screen","ISic001703_tiled.tif","3680px","5520px","I.Sicily with the permission of the Assessorato Regionale dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana - Dipartimento dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana","front","Sicily",{"_":114,"role":115,"ref":116,"museum":117},"Museo Archeologico Regionale Paolo Orsi","museum","http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/museum/097",{"slug":118,"type":115,"name":114,"uri":116,"description":119,"location":120},"097","An outstanding collection of archaeological material. The collection ranges from Siracusa and the surrounding territory (Megara Hyblaia, Akrai, Kasmenai etc) to encompass all of eastern Sicily, reaching as far as Gela and Agrigento. The ground floor covers prehistory through to the end of the Classical period. Upstairs includes Hellenistic and Roman Syracuse and a display of material from the catacombs. A gallery displaying material from Hellenistic eastern Sicily is in preparation.",{"settlement":80,"region":80,"country":121,"address":122,"geo":123},"Italy","Viale Teocrito 66, 96100 - Siracusa",{"lat":124,"lon":125},37.07636989,15.2866213,{"_":127,"type":128},"14930","inventory",{"_":130,"mainLang":131,"languages":132},"Ancient Greek","grc",[130],{"type":134,"bibl":135},"edition",[136],{"author":137,"date":138,"citedRange":139,"ptr":140,"ref":142,"inscriptionDate":138,"title":144,"citation":145,"uri":146,"year":138},"Orsi","1903","col. 386-387 fig.3",{"target":141},"https://www.zotero.org/groups/382445/items/6N8NJ6Y8",{"_":143,"target":143},"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002233","L'Olympieion di Siracusa (scavi del 1893 e 1902)","\u003Cspan>Paolo Orsi, «L’Olympieion di Siracusa (scavi del 1893 e 1902)», \u003Ci>Monumenti Antichi\u003C/i>, Monumenti antichi. Serie monografica, 13 (1903): 369–92\u003C/span>","https://www.zotero.org/groups/isicily/items/6N8NJ6Y8",{"type":148,"bibl":149},"discussion",[150],{"author":151,"date":152,"citedRange":153,"ptr":154,"ref":156,"inscriptionDate":152,"title":158,"citation":159,"uri":160,"year":152},"Dimartino","2011","114",{"target":155},"https://www.zotero.org/groups/382445/items/4S97VREI",{"_":157,"target":157},"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002508","Siracusa. Le fonti epigrafiche","\u003Cspan>A. Dimartino, «Siracusa. Le fonti epigrafiche», in \u003Ci>Siracusa. Immagine e storia di una città\u003C/i> (Pisa, 2011), 59–132; 209–458\u003C/span>","https://www.zotero.org/groups/isicily/items/4S97VREI",{"editor":162,"principal":165,"contributors":166,"change":178},{"_":163,"ref":164},"Jonathan Prag","#JP",{"_":163,"ref":164},[167,170,174],{"_":163,"xml:id":168,"ref":169},"JP","http://orcid.org/0000-0003-3819-8537",{"_":171,"xml:id":172,"ref":173},"Simona Stoyanova","SS","https://orcid.org/0000-0003-3914-9569",{"_":175,"xml:id":176,"ref":177},"Zoé Lienard","ZL","https://orcid.org/0009-0007-0586-7956",{"_":179,"when":180,"who":181},"tagged names and persons","2025-12-24","#ZL","",{"n":106,"url":107,"height":108,"width":109,"desc":110,"surfaceType":111},[],[186],"Orsi, 1903, L'Olympieion di Siracusa (scavi del 1893 e 1902)",[188],"6N8NJ6Y8",[190,191,192,19,24,28,193,194,195,196,194,197,198,131],"isic001703","fragmentary greek inscription",{"_":5},"syracusae","siracusa","sicilia","sicily","museo archeologico regionale paolo orsi","ancient greek",[],{"title":201,"body":202,"divs":203,"editions":228,"images":238,"handnote":244},"ISic001703. Fragmentary Greek inscription","\u003Cdiv id=\"editions\">\u003Cdiv class=\"attribution\">Text encoding: Jonathan Prag\u003C/div>\u003Cdiv id=\"edition-interpretive\" lang=\"grc\">  \u003Cdiv class=\"textpart\" lang=\"grc\">\u003Cspan class=\"ab\" id=\"div-interpretive\">  \u003Ca id=\"al0-interpretive\">\u003C!--0-->\u003C/a>[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>] \u003Cbr id=\"al1-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">1\u003C/span>\u003Cspan data-type=\"persname\" data-name-type=\"divine\" data-text=\"Ἄρτεμις\">\u003Cspan data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"\" data-text=\"Ἄρτεμις\">Ἄρτεμ̣[ις?\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>] \u003Cbr id=\"al2-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">2\u003C/span>\u003Cspan data-type=\"persname\" data-name-type=\"divine\" data-text=\"Διόνυσος\">\u003Cspan data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"\" data-text=\"Διόνυσος\">Διόνυσ[ος?\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>] \u003C/span>\u003C/div>  \u003Cp class=\"miniapp\">\u003C/p>\u003C/div>\u003Cdiv class=\"attribution\">Text encoding: Jonathan Prag\u003C/div>\u003Cdiv id=\"edition-diplomatic\" lang=\"grc\">\u003Cdiv class=\"textpart\" lang=\"grc\">\u003Cspan class=\"ab\" id=\"div-diplomatic\">\u003Ca id=\"al0-diplomatic\">\u003C!--0-->\u003C/a>[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>]\u003Cbr id=\"al1-diplomatic\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">1\u003C/span>\u003Cspan data-type=\"persname\" data-name-type=\"divine\" data-text=\"Ἄρτεμις\">\u003Cspan data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"\" data-text=\"Ἄρτεμις\">ΑΡΤΕ.[..\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>]\u003Cbr id=\"al2-diplomatic\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">2\u003C/span>\u003Cspan data-type=\"persname\" data-name-type=\"divine\" data-text=\"Διόνυσος\">\u003Cspan data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"\" data-text=\"Διόνυσος\">ΔΙΟΝΥΣ[..\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>]\u003C/span>\u003C/div>\u003Cp class=\"miniapp\">\u003C/p>\u003C/div>\u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"facsimile-images\">\u003Ch2>Facsimile Images\u003C/h2>\u003Ca href=\"ISic001703_tiled.tif\">\u003Cimg title=\"I.Sicily with the permission of the Assessorato Regionale dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana - Dipartimento dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana\" src=\"ISic001703_tiled-thumb.tif\">\u003C/a>\u003Ca href=\"ISic001703.jpg\">\u003Cimg title=\"I.Sicily with the permission of the Assessorato Regionale dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana - Dipartimento dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana\" src=\"ISic001703-thumb.jpg\">\u003C/a>\u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"apparatus\">\u003Ch4>Apparatus criticus\u003C/h4>\u003Cul>\u003Cli>\u003Cspan>\u003Cspan>Text after Orsi 1903 fig. 3\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\u003C/li>\u003C/ul>\u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"translation\">\u003Ch2> translation\u003C/h2>\u003Cp class=\"translation-author\">  \u003C/p>\u003Cp>  \u003C/p>\u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"commentary\">\u003Ch2>commentary\u003C/h2>  \u003Cp>Restoration of the names of the divinities Artemis and Dionysos is plausible (even if the case ending can only be hypothetical); but of course other names, of e.g. human dedicants are also possible. The piece is reported by Orsi and listed in the museum inventory, but has not been republished since, nor has it yet been located in the museum. The use of marble (so it is described by Orsi) would be notable for an inscriptional plaque c.300 BCE.\u003C/p>  \u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"bibliography\">\u003Ch2>bibliography\u003C/h2>  \u003Cul>\u003Cli> Orsi 1903 col. 386-387 fig.3 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002233\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002233\u003C/a>\u003C/li>\u003C/ul>  \u003Cul>\u003Cli> Dimartino 2011 114 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002508\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002508\u003C/a>\u003C/li>\u003C/ul>  \u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"handnote\"> \u003Cp>Described by Orsi as fine, small, regular characters of the fourth or third century BCE; Alpha has straight bar; Epsilon has shorter middle bar; omicron is smaller than other characters and mid-line; sigma is four-bar with top and bottom strokes angled moderately outwards, middle strokes extending almost full-width.\u003C/p> Line 1    Interlineation line 1 to 2    \u003C/div>\u003Cdiv id=\"license\"> Licensed under a Creative Commons-Attribution 4.0 licence. \u003C/div>",[204,207,210,213,216,219,222,225],{"id":205,"html":206},"editions","\u003Cdiv class=\"attribution\">Text encoding: Jonathan Prag\u003C/div>\u003Cdiv id=\"edition-interpretive\" lang=\"grc\">  \u003Cdiv class=\"textpart\" lang=\"grc\">\u003Cspan class=\"ab\" id=\"div-interpretive\">  \u003Ca id=\"al0-interpretive\">\u003C!--0-->\u003C/a>[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>] \u003Cbr id=\"al1-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">1\u003C/span>\u003Cspan data-type=\"persname\" data-name-type=\"divine\" data-text=\"Ἄρτεμις\">\u003Cspan data-typ